gomodel:SYNGO_3630  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 14/5/2018 Pim\nrule: NAS_CPLX_2\nrationale: Polyribosomes are present in dendritic spines (PMID:12165474, electron microscopy). The ribosome is the central holoenzyme in the process of \"translation (GO:0006412)\". RLA2 is a generally accepted constituent of the ribosome that together with other ribosomal subunits contributes to the intrinsic activity of the ribosomal complex.. No functions of RLA2 are known independent from the ribosomal complex. Inference to term \"translation (GO:0006412)\" occurs_in \"postsynapse (GO:0098794:)\" is trivial.\nC_ref CC: PMID:12165474 (dendritic spine head)\nP_inf CC: SynGO ID #601\nP_inf CC additional:\n- Distler et al.(2014), PMID:25211037, Table S1, prep:synapse\nComplex membership: RLA2 protein is a fixed member of the 60S ribosomal subunit complex.\n- Shown in crystal structure (PMID:28138070, see Fig.1, name: P2)\n- GO annotations to \"structural constituent of ribosome (GO:0003735)\" (ISO and IEA). Experimental description: Briefly adult mouse brains (2-16 months, 20 animals, 10 g wet weight) were homogenized ... p. 915" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-23" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3630" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

